Scottish First Minister said she would form anti-Tory alliance with Labour and other smaller parties . 
  SNP could win as many as 50 MPs in Scotland - allowing Ed Miliband to become Prime Minister even if he wins fewer votes and MPs than the Tories . 
  Mr Miliband has ruled out going into coalition with the SNP . 
  Nicola Sturgeon said she will help make Mr Miliband PM even if Labour finish 40 seats behind Tories . 
  Comments came as Labour slipped four points behind Tories in polls . 
 